ReutersMessageFormat.name: MarketPrice
ReutersMessageFormat.Description: MarketPrice provides access to trades and quotes from exchanges. It also can provide access to other types of record data that is structured as field-value pairs.

field.name: PERMISSION
field.description: Product permissions information.

field.name: DISPLAYTEMPLATE
field.description: Display information for the IDN terminal device.

field.name: DISPLAY NAME
field.description: Expanded name for the instrument.

field.name: IDN EXCHANGE ID
field.description: Identifier for the exchange on which the instrument trades.

field.name: LAST
field.description: Last trade price or value.

field.name: NET CHANGE
field.description: Difference between latest trading price or value and the historic closing value or settlement price.

field.name: TODAY'S HIGH
field.description: Today's highest transaction value.

field.name: TODAY'S LOW
field.description: Today's lowest transaction value.

field.name: CURRENCY
field.description: The currency in which the instrument is quoted.

field.name: TRADE DATE
field.description: The date of the value in the field TRDPRC_1.

field.name: TRADE TIME
field.description: Time of the value in the TRDPRC_1.

field.name: OPENING PRICE
field.description: Today's opening price or value. The source of this field depends upon the market and instrument type.

field.name: HISTORIC CLOSE
field.description: Most recent non-zero closing value or settlement price.

field.name: BID
field.description: Latest bid price.For US Composite stock and equity market maker super records the best bid price. For OM type option markets the block bid price.

field.name: ASK
field.description: Latest ask price.For US Composite stock and equity market maker super records the best ask price. For OM type option markets the block ask price.

field.name: BID SIZE
field.description: The quantity bid at the latest bid price - in the case of equity market maker super records the total quantity bid at the best bid price. For Australian futures the number of buying contracts.

field.name: ASK SIZE
field.description: The quantity offered at the latest ask price - in the case of equity market maker super records the total quantity offered at the best ask price. For Australian futures the number of selling contracts.

field.name: VOL ACCUMULATED
field.description: Today's total trading volume.

field.name: EARNINGS
field.description: Latest reported earnings per share.

field.name: P E
field.description: Ratio of stock price to earnings per share.

field.name: DIVIDEND DATE
field.description: Date on which dividend will be paid.

field.name: EX DIV DATE
field.description: The date on which the issue will trade ex-dividend.

field.name: TRADE EXCH ID
field.description: Exchange identifier of the latest trade.US Composites only.

field.name: CLOSE BID
field.description: Last bid price of the day. For US Composites the last best bid price.

field.name: CLOSE ASK
field.description: Last ask price of the day. For US Composites the last best ask price.

field.name: OPEN INTEREST
field.description: Open interest. The total number of option or futures contracts that have not been closed or in the case of commodities liquidated or offset by delivery.

field.name: STRIKE PRICE
field.description: Strike price; the price at which an option is exercisable.

field.name: EXPIRE DATE
field.description: The date on which the future option or warrant expires.

field.name: MATURITY DATE
field.description: The date on which a bond matures.

field.name: COUPON RATE
field.description: The interest rate assigned to a bond when it is issued.

field.name: SETTLEMENT PRC
field.description: Settlement price. The official closing price of a futures or option contract set by the clearing house at the end of the trading day.

field.name: DIVIDEND
field.description: The latest reported dividend to be paid per share to shareholders.

field.name: UPPER TRD LIMIT
field.description: Upper trading limit for today's trading.

field.name: LOWER TRD LIMIT
field.description: Lower limit for today's trading.

field.name: NUMBER TRADES
field.description: Number of trades today. For indices the number of tmes the index has been calculated.

field.name: OFFICIAL CODE
field.description: Unique numeric code assigned to the instrument.

field.name: HIST CLOSE DATE
field.description: Date of the most recent non-zero closing price as held in HST_CLOSE FID 20 and HST_CLOSE2 FID 963.

field.name: TURNOVER
field.description: The daily turnover revenue or value of all shares for either a particular instrument or an exchange. Currently supplied by New Zealand SE Hong Kong SE and Copenhagen SE. Cleared during the pre-market clear. The value is scaled according to the field TN

field.name: ISSUE DATE
field.description: The date on which the bond prospectus was issued.

field.name: PUT/CALL FLAG
field.description: Indicates whether option is a put or a call.

field.name: NAV:NT ASSET VL
field.description: Net asset value for US over the counter mutual funds.

field.name: MARKET STAT
field.description: Indicates the current futures market status including whether a fast market condition exists.

field.name: MID-PRICE
field.description: The mid-price between the bid and ask prices supplied by the London ISE. Cleared during the pre-market clear.

field.name: OFFICIAL CLS
field.description: Today's official closing price reported for Italian equities.

field.name: NAV DATE
field.description: Date of net asset value.

field.name: SELLER ID
field.description: Codes identifying the broker on the buy/sell side of a trade reported by the Consolidated Canadian ticker CCN.

field.name: TRADE VOL
field.description: Transactional volume of the trade price reported in TRDPRC_1.

field.name: OPEN XID
field.description: For US composite quotes the exchange identifier of the exchange where the opening price was made.

field.name: BID TIME
field.description: Time of the latest update to the BID field FID 22.

field.name: ASK TIME
field.description: Time of the latest update to the ASK field FID 25.

field.name: IRG PRICE
field.description: A cancelled inserted retransmitted or irregular price.

field.name: IRG VOLUME
field.description: The volume associated with the price held in the field IRGPRC (FID 372).

field.name: IRG PRICE TYPE
field.description: An indicator of the type of price held in the field IRGPRC (FID 372).

field.name: PRC CORRECT TIME
field.description: The time of a price correction - the time of update to either the IRGPRC (FID 372) or INSPRC (FID 376) fields.

field.name: LAST TIME
field.description: Time of the last trade with precision in seconds - the time of the last update to the field TRDPRC_1 (FID 6).

field.name: VOL ACC 2
field.description: The previous day's accumulated volume.

field.name: VOLUME DATE
field.description: The date when a particular volume occurred at present that held in HST_VOL.

field.name: IRGBUY
field.description: Canadian Equity Exchanges 'New Buyer' field for 'not last' trades/cancellation messages.

field.name: IRGSELL
field.description: Canadian Equity Exchanges 'New Seller' field for 'not last' trades/cancellation messages.

field.name: UPC-71 RSTRCTED
field.description: A flag which indicates whether or not a Nasdaq security is UPC-71 "RESTRICTED".

field.name: COLID 7
field.description: Sixth & seventh colour indicators. Similar to COLID_1.

field.name: SOURCE FEED NME
field.description: Source feed name.

field.name: SHRS OUTSDING
field.description: Total value of outstanding shares.

field.name: SECURITY NAME
field.description: The complete name of the security.

field.name: SECURITY ISSUER
field.description: Issuer of the security.

field.name: SHORT DESCRIPTN
field.description: Short Description - short item description.

field.name: INSTRUMENT CLASS
field.description: Instrument classification

field.name: DISPLAY NAME 2
field.description: Display Name 2

field.name: ISSUER DOMOCILE
field.description: The country a company/entity originates from.

field.name: OFFICIAL CLOSE
field.description: The official closing price from Exchange

field.name: RECORD DATE
field.description: Record date.

field.name: BOND TICKER
field.description: The ticker associated with a bond issue

field.name: TIMCOR MS
field.description: Millisecond time FIDs.

field.name: SOURCE ASK PRICE
field.description: Source IDs for Ask Prices. Use same Enum table as TRDXID_1 (FID 44)

field.name: SOURCE BID PRICE
field.description: Source IDs for Bid Prices. Use same Enum table as TRDXID_1 (FID 44)

field.name: TICK:UP/DOWN
field.description: The direction of trading from the previous trade.

field.name: EXCHANGE TIME
field.description: The exchange time with precision in seconds

field.name: INSERT PRICE
field.description: When an exchange sends a correction report with details of both the cancelled and inserted price this field holds the inserted price.

field.name: INSERT VOLUME
field.description: The volume associated with the price held in the field INSPRC (FID 376).

field.name: INSERT PRC TYPE
field.description: An indication of the type of price held in the field INSPRC (FID 376).

field.name: EXCHANGE ID 2
field.description: Identifier for the exchange on which the instrument trades. This field is a two-byte replacement for FID4 RDN_EXCHID and contains a super-set of this field's range of values.

field.name: PREF DISP TMPLT
field.description: The 'preferred' display template number.

field.name: OPN NET CH
field.description: Difference between open price and the previous close price.

field.name: OFF CD IND
field.description: An indication of the source of the code in the official code field OFFCL_CODE FID 78.

field.name: IRGXID
field.description: This field will be used to transmit the Exchange Identifier of all CTS trades designated as 'not last' trades.

field.name: CTS QUALIFIER
field.description: For US stock the CTS ticker price qualifier.

field.name: SEQNUM
field.description: This field contains the message sequence number. For NMTS this is a six-digit number.

field.name: BLOCK COUNT
field.description: Number of block trades today.

field.name: PRNTBCK
field.description: A field transmitted by RQS on receipt of a correction message from SIAC containing the 'print back' count. This count is derived by SIAC and directly references the erroneous print received from the participating Exchange.

field.name: BLOCK VOLUME
field.description: Today's total block trading volume.Updated whenever a trade of over 10 000 shares occurs.

field.name: BID NET CHANGE
field.description: The difference between the latest bid and the historic closing bid.

field.name: QUOTIM
field.description: Quote time given in seconds.

field.name: TICK:BID
field.description: The direction of bidding from the previous bid. Can be calculated from either the bid price or for forward rates the offset from the bid price.

field.name: CUM/EX MARKER
field.description: Cum/ex security marker.

field.name: PRICE CODE
field.description: Price qualifier code for equities bonds and options

field.name: VOLUME1xPRICE1
field.description: Numeric field to contain a value equivalent to the product of latest trade volume and latest trade price (TRDVOL_1 x TRDPRC_1).

field.name: RECORDTYPE
field.description: Field which indicates the type of record and also the type of data in that record.

field.name: TRADING UNITS
field.description: The price units in which the issue trades.

field.name: PERCENT CHANGE
field.description: Percentage change in the latest trade price or value from the historic close.

field.name: PRICE CODE 2
field.description: Second price qualifier code. Defined for US Government securities.

field.name: PROVIDER SYMBOL
field.description: Original symbol of tradable entity provided by exchange/contributor.

field.name: ADJUSTED CLOSE
field.description: The last value available for close which is stored for Graphics also adjusted for capital changes.

field.name: HIST CLOSE BID
field.description: The historic closing bid i.e. the last non-zero closing bid.

field.name: HIST CLS BID DT
field.description: The historic closing bid date.
